               <note type="editions">Critical Edition, alongside an Urdu translation, published by The Ibn ʿArabī Foundation (Rawalpindi, Pakistan, 2012). Ed. Abrār Aḥmad Shāhī.</note>
               <note type="translations">There is no complete translation of this work. The following cover only four of its five parts. Partial English translation (middle section) by R W J Austin: Sufis of Andalusia, London, 1971; reprinted Hawick, 2001. Partial English translation (first and last sections) by Roger Boase and Farid Sahnoun: ‘Excerpts from the Epistle on the Spirit of Holiness’ in Muhyiddin Ibn ʿArabī (1165-1240), Ed. Stephen Hirtenstein and Michael Tiernan, Oxford, 1993. Partial French translation by R W J Austin; Gérard Lecomte: Les Soufis d'Andalousie : (Rûh al-quds et ad-Durrat al-fâkhirah), Paris 1979; 1988.</note>
               <note type="translationsEur">Partial Spanish translations by Miguel Asín Palacios: Vidas de Santones Andaluces, Madrid, 1935. Partial Spanish translation of Part 3 by Miguel Asín Palacios: Risalat al-Quds, Madrid 1939. Partial Spanish translation by R W J Austin, David García Valverde: Los Sufis de Andalucia, Malaga, 1990. Partial German translation by Alma Geise: Ibn ʿArabī: Urwolke und Welt, Munich 2002.</note>
